&lt;h1&gt;Medical secretary&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Hughenden Valley Surgery&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The closing date is 30 November 2020&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job overview&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in our small team of 3 medical secretaries but as part of our wider friendly Clinical and Administration team at Hughenden Valley Surgery that covers 2 sites in High Wycombe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own desk, free parking, NHS pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Main duties of the job&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;referrals to secondary care using the NHS e-referral system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Typing of letters&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looking after the admin email address, answering emails, forwarding for action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Speaking with patients to chase referrals and give advice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Keeping up to date with latest systems and ways of working within the NHS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About us&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hughenden Valley Surgery has just under 13,000 patients based over 2 sites. Large friendly workforce both clinical and administrative&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job of medical secretary has evolved from &#39;typing letters&#39;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need good computer skills and be proficient in Word &amp; excel. Training on our EMIS system will be part of your induction. Excellent telephone manner essential. Organised and methodical in your work highly desirable but also with the ability to solve problems andprioritiseworkloads.&lt;/p&gt;
